From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000024 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 23:55:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: OMAP4: cpuidle: register C1 (WFI) only on steelhead

The SMP bring-up (patch 0009) disabled cpuidle wholesale with
cpuidle.off=1 on the cmdline, because the C2/C3 MPUSS power transitions
trap into the HS secure monitor and fault with the second core online
(stock 3.0.8 guards the same paths with cpuidle44xx.disallow_smp_idle).
The blanket switch made cpuidle_register() fail, logging

  failed to register cpuidle driver

on every boot, and left the CPUs idling via the bare arch_cpu_idle WFI
fallback with no residency accounting.

Do what stock actually does instead: keep the cpuidle driver but limit
steelhead to C1 -- omap_enter_idle_simple() is a plain WFI with no
MPUSS power transition and no secure SMC, so it is exactly as safe as
the fallback while restoring a registered driver, per-state residency
stats and governor behaviour. The cpuidle.off=1 cmdline switch is
dropped from the defconfig in the same batch.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/cpuidle44xx.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/cpuidle44xx.c
@@ -11,6 +11,7 @@
 #include <linux/cpuidle.h>
 #include <linux/cpu_pm.h>
 #include <linux/export.h>
+#include <linux/of.h>
 #include <linux/tick.h>
 
 #include <asm/cpuidle.h>
@@ -326,5 +327,20 @@
 	if (!cpu_clkdm[0] || !cpu_clkdm[1])
 		return -ENODEV;
 
+	/*
+	 * steelhead (HS OMAP4460): deep C-states fault - the MPUSS power
+	 * transitions of C2/C3 trap into the secure monitor, which the HS
+	 * secure side rejects with SMP online (the stock 3.0.8 kernel guarded
+	 * the same paths with its cpuidle44xx.disallow_smp_idle parameter).
+	 * Register C1 only: omap_enter_idle_simple() is a plain WFI with no
+	 * MPUSS power transition and no secure SMC. This replaces the earlier
+	 * blanket cpuidle.off=1 cmdline (which made cpuidle_register() fail
+	 * with "failed to register cpuidle driver" every boot), restoring a
+	 * real cpuidle driver - proper idle residency accounting and governor
+	 * behaviour - at identical safety.
+	 */
+	if (of_machine_is_compatible("google,steelhead"))
+		idle_driver->state_count = 1;
+
 	return cpuidle_register(idle_driver, cpu_online_mask);
 }
